  * Collaborate with a talented Software Engineering team in Bank Technology 
  * Leverage your expertise in Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) to contribute to our dynamic team 
  * Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne location & enjoy extensive staff benefits & flexibility 

** About the role **

We're seeking a talented Software Engineer to join our team, with a strong
background in Adobe Experience Manager (AEM). In this role, you'll collaborate
with Tribe/Platform leaders and the Engineering Practice to enhance our
Engineering capability across people, tools, culture, and work practices.

The primary objective of this role is to establish capability for Suncorp Bank
in managing the Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) asset. This asset is crucial
for providing analytics and content management functionality for the Internet
Banking application.

** What you’ll do **

  * Collaborates effectively across teams and with customers, prioritising customer needs and placing them at the forefront of decision-making 
  * Clarifies what’s expected, taking accountability to resolve problems, and set high personal standards to deliver timely results in a changing environment 
  * Builds strong relationships and fosters effective teamwork, prioritising learning and development, and taking action to promote safety and well-being 
  * Ensures the quality of data input and actively identifies risks and issues 
  * Participate in, or delivers, Approvals to Act, Security Reviews and Secure Development Lifecycle 

** What you’ll bring **

  * 4+ years professional software engineering experience 
  * Extensive expertise in Adobe Experience Manager as a Cloud Service (AEMaaCS) 
  * Deep understanding of Data Model and AEM Data Integration, adaptive forms, form components, and site page creation 
  * Skilled in developing with Java or Javascript to interface with downstream RESTful API integrations 
  * Hands-on experience using forms with OAuth2 / SAML authentication patterns 
  * Proficient in developing UI components utilising a Javascript framework (e.g., ReactJS), along with HTML, CSS, and LESS 
  * Demonstrated experience integrating AEM with Adobe Test and Target and Adobe Analytics 

** What we can offer you **

  * Competitive benefits package and excellent work culture 
  * Excellent discounts on a range of retail favourite stores as well as banking and insurance products 
  * A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave 
  * Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs 
  * Give back to our communities with payroll giving, donation matching and paid volunteer leave 

** About Suncorp Group **

We’re proud to be a part of the Suncorp Group family alongside some of
Australia’s most trusted and diverse names in insurance. Together, we share a
drive to make the complex simple and bring our customers peace of mind when it
matters most – while helping to evolve and innovate the ways we can serve our
community every day. That comes with all kinds of exciting opportunities for
you to grow your own career. Whether you’re guiding people through life’s
biggest moments or providing them with support in times they need it most,
you’ll be driven forward by our shared customer obsession and supported at
every step of the journey.

